# ─── Request & Processing Logging ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Configure your logging infrastructure below

# Local log file written by the API and tailed by Promtail
LOG_FILE_PATH=tmp/logs/api.log

# Log Level
LOG_LEVEL=info
LOG_IGNORED_CONTEXTS=InstanceLoader
LOG_FILE_MAX_SIZE_BYTES=10485760
LOG_FILE_MAX_FILES=5

# ─── Prometheus Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prometheus metrics are automatically enabled in production
# No additional configuration needed - metrics are exposed at /metrics endpoint

# ─── Notes ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Request logging is automatic via RequestLoggingMiddleware
#    - Logs all HTTP requests with user info, duration, status
#    - Writes JSON to tmp/logs/api.log for Promtail/Loki ingestion
#    - In-memory cache for dashboard queries
#
# 2. Processing logs track video/audio/image generation
#    - Automatic logging in all queue processors
#    - Includes job IDs, duration, status, and errors
#    - Metrics synced to Prometheus
#
# 3. Dashboard available at /admin/monitoring
#    - Real-time request and processing logs
#    - User activity overview
#    - Filters: user ID, method, job type, status
#    - Auto-refreshes every 5 seconds
#
# 4. API Endpoints:
#    - GET /admin/logs/requests      - Request logs with filters
#    - GET /admin/logs/processing    - Processing logs with filters
#    - GET /admin/logs/stats         - Aggregated statistics
#
# 5. Grafana Integration:
#    - Configure Loki datasource: http://localhost:3100
#    - Query examples:
#      {service="multilingual-tales-api"} |= "error"
#      {service="multilingual-tales-api", level="error"}
#      {service="multilingual-tales-api"} | json | userId="user123"
